genresAdvancedInfo.name: karen pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Karen pop is a genre of music that originated from the Karen people of Myanmar. It is characterized by its unique blend of traditional Karen music with modern pop elements, resulting in catchy and upbeat tunes. Karen pop often features the use of traditional instruments such as the saung gauk (harp) and the kay thwe (drum), as well as electronic beats and synthesizers.
